  "decision": {
    "status": "reject_panel_owned_contribution_producer",
    "reason": "The full-D16 prepacked panel producer is 110-130 ms at S4096, over 12x slower than the current sparse-atomic dKV slice, even though it does not write dKV. Increasing the K tile from 16 to 32 or 64 does not materially improve it.",
    "candidate_refinement": "Keep the existing fast query-major dot-K/MFMA contribution producer shape. Use prepacked or compact route metadata only after contribution math, for in-producer grouped/segmented reduction or a reduced write path.",
    "next_kernel_target": "Modify the retained dot_k_atomic-style producer so it computes grad_logits^T q + probs^T dO once per query-major tile, then performs lane/warp/tile-local segmented accumulation before global dKV writes. Do not move the producer to token-panel/group-panel ownership."
  },
